                     GEOGRAPHIC RESTRICTIONS NOTICE

Residents of any countries, states, or territories that require age
verification for software usage are NOT authorized to use Bytedock.

This restriction currently applies to the following jurisdictions:
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Brazil — effective March 17, 2026
  • The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland: Online Safety Act — Effective July 25, 2025
  • State of Texas: The App Store Accountability Act — Effective Jan 1, 2026
  • State of Utah: Utah Caregiver/Minor App Store Act — Effective May 7, 2026
  • State of Louisiana: App Store Accountability Act — Effective July 1, 2026
  • State of California: Digital Age Assurance Act — Effective Jan 1, 2027
  • Any other country, state, or terrority that require age verification for software usage

This restriction will additionally apply to the following jurisdictions
if their currently proposed legislation is enacted into law:

  • List will be updated as needed.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  NOTE: This list will be updated as needed, if you have any questions please
contact your senator (202) 224-3121 or https://www.badinternetbills.com/
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The Bytedock project urges all affected users to contact their elected
representatives and advocate for the repeal or replacement of these laws.
Age verification mandates for general-purpose software represent a
significant threat to digital privacy, free expression, and open-source
development. Your voice matters. Call your U.S Senator, this is proably
not going to do anything but you can say at least you tried. The United 
States Senator Switch board opeartor phone number is (202) 224-3121.

This list is subject to change as legislation is enacted, amended, or
repealed. Users are responsible for ensuring their use of Bytedock
complies with the laws of their jurisdiction.

